args:
A sudden rash of tears in space remind the
prince and his friends of a time they were
visited by great heroes from another world.
When they travel to the gate that connects to
that world, they encounter Sharena, princess
of the Askran Kingdom.
Replete with gates leading to all manner of worlds,\nZenith calls heroes from across time and space.
It is a world under constant threat from\notherworldly forces, and one where\nviolent warfare is a fact of life.

It hosts a kingdom of flame that seeks to render
all unto ash, and a realm of death that ravages
life itself. While in heaven above, gods from
ancient folklore continue their reigns...
What are you scheming this time, Thórr?
All is as my master desires, for I am\nbut an implement of His lofty will.
Prince Alfonse of Askr, he who can open\ngateways to the realms, I would have you\noffer your vessel to my master.
Do not awaken yourself anytime soon;\nI will attend to your worldly form.
Where are you taking my brother?!

And the princess of gateways as well!
Well then, know that I intend to judge the
worthiness of certain otherworldly heroes
as warriors for the heavens.
And for that purpose, I have chosen\nto borrow your brother's power.
I may not follow everything you're saying,\nbut I can't stand the way you strut about\ndoing whatever you please!
Human beings aren't playthings to be\nbroken out at the whims of the gods!

Surely you realize the strength of your
souls surpasses the power of us gods?
This is the weapon granted you that
you may have the ability to defy us.
If you seek to thwart our will and have \nspirit enough to challenge its might,\nthen by all means, follow me...
Follow me to the dragonblood realm!
I know the gate was around here\nsomewhere...
Ooo! Ooo! I think this is it!
Yeah, that looks like the spot, all right.\n'Course all I'm seein' is a buncha ruins...
I don't sense any power here now.\nIt seems unlikely that the gate has\nseen recent use.
But all the tears in space we've seen\nlately MUST be connected to this gate!\n...Er, right?

While we've no specific evidence of such
a connection, a similar phenomenon did
occur when Prince Alfonse's group first
arrived in this world.
Yeah, I'd hoped we'd find a clue here,\nbut maybe it's... Huh?
That light... The gate is opening!
It's open! Commander Anna, it's open!\nBut goodness, it appears to be unstable.\nI must hurry through at once.
Hey, you guys all hear a voice from\nthe other side of the gate, right?
I may not get another chance at this,\nso if I have to go through alone,\nthat's what I'm going to do!
I made it! ...Er, at least, I think so?\nIs this the dragonblood realm?
You're the seventh scion of the\nAlberian throne, aren't you?
You're just as my brother\nsaid you would be.
Your brother...? Wait, are you\nPrince Alfonse's younger sister?
I sure am! Princess Sharena of the\nAskran Kingdom, at your service!
I can't even tell you what an honor\nthis is for me, Prince. I've been a fan\nof yours for decades.
I'm sorry. Did you say DECADES?
Well, perhaps not in a literal sense,\nbut it certainly feels like it.
Riiight. Well, um, I'm very pleased to\nmeet you as well, Princess Sharena.
Damn, when Alfonse said he and his\nlittle sis had different temperaments,\nhe wasn't jokin' around!
Oh, I think me and her are gonna\nget along like a house on fire!
You must be Notte the faerie! Alfonse told\nme the faeries here were small, but I had\nno idea you were THIS small!
Guys! Emergency! We got rifts\nopening up all over Rovetelle!
Not MORE of the damn things!

Hold on to your butts, 'cause it gets worse:
These rifts aren't closing, AND a buncha
fiends are pouring out of 'em and headin'
for the city!
In that case, we'll head there right away.\n...I'm sorry, Princess. I know we have a\nlot to discuss, but I'm needed—
Let me join you, please. I mean,\nI'm probably the reason this whole\nmess is happening in the first place.
Do you think this is related to your\nfamily's power to open gateways?
Short answer? Yes.\nLong answer? It's complicated.
Then it's all the more important we not\nexpose you to danger; we must find a\nway to get you to safety at once.
You don't have to worry about me.\nI'm a member of the Order of Heroes,\nand I know my way around a fight.
In that case, we'd be happy for your help.
If half of what Prince Alfonse told me\nabout his sister is true, then she's\ngoing to be a very powerful ally.
Plus, it'll be easier to protect the lady\nif she's hangin' within sword's reach.
